Perfect! I now have all the information needed to provide a complete analysis. Let me compile my findings.

## Investigation Results

I've thoroughly examined the Lexical editor configuration across your codebase. Here are my findings:

### 1. **App.jsx** - Main LexicalComposer Theme (Lines 52-65)

The main theme **DOES include text format class mappings**:

```javascript
const theme = {
  paragraph: 'editor-paragraph',
  heading: {
    h1: 'editor-heading-h1',
    h2: 'editor-heading-h2',
    h3: 'editor-heading-h3',
  },
  quote: 'editor-quote',
  text: {
    bold: 'editor-text-bold',
    italic: 'editor-text-italic',        // <-- PRESENT
    underline: 'editor-text-underline',   // <-- PRESENT
  }
}
```

This is the theme that wraps the entire app (line 79), so it should apply globally.

### 2. **RichTextEditor.jsx** - Confirmed Issue

The local theme in RichTextEditor.jsx (lines 35-38) **does NOT include text format mappings**:

```javascript
const theme = {
    paragraph: 'editor-paragraph',
    heading: 'editor-heading',
}
```

This is a problem if this component is being used for editing and it's overriding the global theme from App.jsx.

### 3. **editJournal.jsx** - Correct Implementation

The theme in editJournal.jsx (lines 24-37) **DOES include complete text format mappings**:

```javascript
const theme = {
    paragraph: 'editor-paragraph',
    heading: { h1, h2, h3 },
    quote: 'editor-quote',
    text: {
        bold: 'editor-text-bold',
        italic: 'editor-text-italic',
        underline: 'editor-text-underline',
    }
}
```

### 4. **ContentView.jsx** - Correct Implementation

The theme in ContentView.jsx (lines 78-91) **DOES include complete text format mappings** for read-only viewers.

### 5. **editor.css** - CSS Rules Confirmed

The CSS file at `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\Editor\editor.css` **does have the correct formatting rules** (lines 1-10):

```css
.editor-text-bold {
    font-weight: bold;
}
.editor-text-italic {
    font-style: italic;
}
.editor-text-underline {
    text-decoration: underline;
}
```

No conflicting CSS rules found. The font styling appears clean without font-family overrides that would prevent italic variants.

### 6. **Toolbar.jsx** - Dispatch Mechanism Verified

The toolbar correctly dispatches FORMAT_TEXT_COMMAND (line 174):

```javascript
const applyTextFormat = (format) => {
    editor.dispatchCommand(FORMAT_TEXT_COMMAND, format)
}
```

And the italic button properly calls this (line 341):

```javascript
<div onClick={() => applyTextFormat('italic')} className={getBtnClass(activeStates.italic)} title="Italic">
```

The active state detection is also correct (line 113):

